file.name: api.yaml
file.content:
openapi: 3.0.3
info:
  title: Hello Spring
  description:
    A minimal "Hello, world" FOLIO module written in Java, inspired by the `hello-vertx` example.
  license:
    name: Apache License 2.0
    url: https://spdx.org/licenses/Apache-2.0
  version: v1.0
paths:
  /hello:
    get:
      summary: Get "Hello, World!"
      responses:
        "200":
          description: The traditional greeting
          content:
            text/plain:
              schema:
                type: string
                example: "Hello, World!\n"
    post:
      summary: Send data to be wrapped up in a response object.
      requestBody:
        description: Data to be wrapped up in response object
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              type: object
              example:
                123:
                  - a
                  - b
                  - c
      responses:
        "200":
          description: The supplied data wrapped up in a JSON object
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                type: object
                properties:
                  greeting:
                    type: string
                  data:
                    type: object
                example:
                  greeting: "Hello, World!\n"
                  data:
                    123:
                      - a
                      - b
                      - c

Error: notImplemented: path "/hello": get: responses: 200: contents: unsupported content types: [text/plain]
